{"type":"step-attempt","step":"code-review","sessionId":"7c58d885-a5f0-4267-aee8-7e8ff52daa6a","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/scope-exceeded-escalation/review-feedback-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/step/executor.ts","title":"Redundant condition: (isJudgeStep || isConformanceStep) is equivalent to isJudgeStep","rationale":"isJudgeStep (line 642) already includes isConformanceStep via `|| isConformanceStep`. The OR condition on line 659 is a no-op. No behavioral impact.","line":659},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"tests/unit/core/step/scope-escalation.test.ts","title":"TC-023 (must): resumePoint.step assertion is indirect — manually injected, not read from finalState","rationale":"TC-023 requires asserting that resumePoint.step equals the checkpoint after breach. The test manually injects resumePoint into getOpenDecisionFindings rather than asserting finalState.resumePoint?.step. Since executor.execute() does not run Pipeline.escalate(), the Pipeline-level resumePoint assignment is not verified end-to-end. Behavior is correct (verdict=escalation is confirmed), and existing pipeline tests cover escalation→awaiting-resume chain, but the specific assertion is missing.","line":530},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"tests/unit/core/pipeline/compose-reviewers.test.ts","title":"TC-020 (should): no test that composeReviewerDescriptor preserves permissionScope from base","rationale":"TC-020 (should priority) is not implemented. The spread `{ ...base }` in composeReviewerDescriptor naturally propagates permissionScope, but there is no explicit test. No current behavioral impact since no registry profile declares permissionScope.","line":1}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-13T15:35:49.317Z","endedAt":"2026-06-13T15:42:23.541Z"}
